When your coach captures a picture of you and well you steal it !!! It's how we do.. 😜😜 It was super scary going facebook live... But it was fun and such a rush too!!! Isn't Kayla beautiful!  She is so inspiring to me as well as our ENTIRE team!

There was few blips on the call..
I had to use my hubbies login since I was banned on FB again..✅
For whatever reason I couldn't add my other coach on the call..✅ But ya know we rocked it out regardless and I had so much fun doing it.. That's the fun, failing forward and finding a way in anything!! 🙌🏼 I gotta tell ya, sharing your journey is never easy, but the messages received makes it so worth it.. When someone tells you they are losing weight, getting stronger, building their confidence.. EVERY SINGLE MESSAGE IS WORTH IT!

Our dreams matter.. So does yours!

If you want to watch the video.. Send me a DM and I'll send it to you!

AND.. if you are ready to join us, send me a message and let's do this crazy beautiful dream together!! 💌emylougall@gmail.com💌

NEVER STOP DREAMING!! #joinus #youareworthit .

Life is filled with roads, diverging and intersecting. Each choice leading you down a path, on a journey, the future unbeknownst to you. 
Yet we travel even when we hope to still ourselves body, mind and spirit life drags us on. Forward we move, willing or unwilling we move, we move because to be alive is to constantly be in motion, thinking, feeling, hurting, achieving.

Where do I begin?  I feel SO overwhelmed!  I begin right here, right now, IN the present moment, WITH the present moment.  There will be additions and deletions, failures and successes.  I just need to start where I am and move.  My story is unfolding one by one.  One experience, one exploration.  One thought, one word. One paragraph, one post.  I remind myself to be patient with the process.  All will fall into place. . . and most likely not as I forecast.
.
The empowerment comes from moving.
.
Sometimes I do not know where to begin.  Sometimes I do not know where to move.  I know if I stay where I am today, tomorrow I will still be there.  I want to create my life.  Move step by step.  The journey will be imperfect. Perfectly imperfect!  Perfectly imperfect!!
.
